This paper focuses on wireless networks and their vulnerability to adversarial jamming, which falls under the category of network security. The paper proposes resource competitive algorithms for the broadcast problem, which involves disseminating a message to all nodes in the network, and this falls under the category of distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
